RICAN LIBRARY SCENE (IMPRESSIONS OF AMERICAN LIBRARIES AND LIBRARIANS).     A USSR LIBRARIAN, FOR 8 YEARS (1970-78) THE DIRECTOR OF THE UN LIBRARY IN NEWYORK, DESCRIBES IMPRESSIONS MADE ON HER BY US LIBRARIES AND US LIBRARY LIFE.DEPENDENCE OF BOTH PUBLIC AND RESEARCH LIBRARIES ON PRIVATE CAPITAL IS THEREASON FOR THEIR UNEVEN DEVELOPMENT THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY. MODERN LIBRARYEQUIPMENT IN BOTH SMALL AND LARGE LIBRARIES, AUTOMATION, DEVELOPMENT OFINTEGRATED LIBRARY SYSTEMS AND LIBRARY COOPERATION ARE SEEN AS THE MAINACHIEVEMENTS. LIBRARY ADMINISTRATION, MANAGEMENT, PERSONNEL (WITH SPECIALREFERENCE TO THE STATUS OF WOMEN), EDUCATION, EMPLOYMENT SITUATION, THE ROLEOF LIBRARY ASSOCIATIONS IN US LIBRARIANSHIP, AND LIBRARY CONFERENCES AND THEIRORGANISATION ARE DISCUSSED